
This directory is only for UI *and* OS independent code. 

It can only rely on ANSI C and FrexxEd/FPL API's apart from the 
exceptions listed below. It should not contain code that assumes a GUI

Small shims/wrappers are provided for the exceptions listed
below, in order to ease portability.

The following AmigaOS API calls are OK to use:

    AllocMem()
    FreeMem()

The following AmigaOS types are OK to use, but avoid when possible:

    BOOL

The following POSIX functions are OK to use

    POSIX           AmigaOS Equivalent
    strcasecmp      Stricmp
    strncasecmp     Strnicmp

